main event: A witness observed an object in the sky believed to be a satellite on October 26, 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared to be moving rapidly in a straight line across the sky,The observer described the object as looking like a regular star but closer,The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes,The object moved in a northeasterly direction,The report concluded the object was a satellite.
witness description: the witness described the object as a star-like object that was closer and moved rapidly
